name: Scapular Push-Ups
cues: Keep elbows completely straight and locked out.

name: Incline Bench Press
precautions: Do not lock elbows out at the top.
cues: Retract and depress shoulder blades.
Drive the dumbbells up and slightly inward.

name: Flat Bench Press
precautions: Do not bounce the bar off the chest.
Do not flare elbows excessively.
Do not lock elbows out at the top.
cues: Think about bending the bar to retract and depress shoulder blades.
Keep feet flat on the floor to maintain leg drive.

name: Decline Push-Ups
precautions: Do not do it on an unstable elevated surface.
Do not let the body sag.
cues: Keep your core and glutes tight.
Lower your chest until it's just above the floor.

name: Medicine Ball Chest Pass
precautions: Do not do it in a conjusted space.
cues: Load the ball close to your chest.
Explode forward using the chest and triceps.
Follow through with your arms completely.

name: Lu Raises
precautions: Do not use heavy weights.
Do not shrug the shoulders up.
cues: Keep a neutral grip (thumbs slightly up).
Focus on controlled movement, especially on the descent.

name: Close-Grip Push-Ups
precautions: Do not let the elbows flare out.
cues: Keep your core tight and back flat.
Lower slowly until your chest lightly touches your thumbs.

name: Single-Leg RDL
precautions: Do not use heavy weights.
Do not round the lower back.
cues: Hinge at the hip, imagining closing a car door with the non-working leg.
Keep a firm, slight bend in the standing knee.
Focus on pushing the non-working leg straight back, not just lowering the torso.

name: Pull-Ups
precautions: Do not kip.
cues: Initiate pull with the shoulders (depress and retract).
Imagine pulling the elbows to the hips.

name: Conventional Deadlift
precautions: Do not round the lower back.
cues: Push the floor away (legs).
Keep chest up and shoulders back.
Finish by squeezing the glutes, not leaning back.

name: Deadhang
cues: Fully relax the shoulders.

name: Lower Back Hyperextensions
precautions: Do not over-extend the spine past a neutral straight line.
cues: Squeeze the glutes at the top.

name: Wide-Grip Cable Rows
precautions: Do not lean back excessively.
Do not use momentum to pull the weight.
cues: Pull elbows wide and back.
Squeeze the shoulder blades together.
Maintain an upright torso.

name: Lat Pulldowns
precautions: Do not lean back too far.
cues: Pull the bar down toward the upper chest.
Initiate the pull by driving the elbows down.
Maintain a slight arch in the lower back.

name: Smith Machine Shrugs
precautions: Do not roll the shoulders; move straight up and down.
Do not use excessive weight that compromises range of motion.
cues: Keep arms straight.
Shrug the shoulders straight up to the ears.
Squeeze and hold at the peak contraction.

name: Band Pull-Aparts
precautions: Do not shrug the shoulders up.
cues: Keep arms mostly straight and level with the floor.
Squeeze shoulder blades together forcefully.

name: Band Pull-Apart Hold
cues: Retract the scapula while pulling the band apart.
Keep arms level with the floor.

name: External Shoulder Rotation (Elbow On Knee)
precautions: Do not use heavy weight.
Do not do it uncontrolled.
cues: Keep the elbow stable on the knee.
Rotate the forearm only, moving the dumbbell up and down.

name: Trap Bar Deadlift Jumps
precautions: Do not use heavy weight.
Do not land on balls of feet.
cues: Land on toes.
Leave the ground slightly at the peak extension.
Maintain upright torso throughout.

name: Trap Bar Deadlift
precautions: Do not bend the lower back.
Do not make the lift jerky.
cues: Push the floor away with the legs (quad-drive).
Keep the chest up.
Stand tall and squeeze the glutes at the top.

name: Incline Y-Raises
precautions: Do not use heavy weights.
Do not shrug the shoulders up.
cues: Lie face down on an incline bench.
Raise arms in a 'Y' shape.
Focus on upward rotation of the scapula.

name: Chin-Ups
precautions: Do not kip.
Do not let the elbows flare out.
cues: Use a supinated (underhand) grip.
Pull the chest toward the bar.
Focus on driving the elbows down and back.

name: Cossack Squats
precautions: Do not let the working knee collapse inward.
Do not force depth if groin mobility is limited.
cues: Keep the non-working leg straight with toes pointed up.
Maintain a neutral spine in the squat position.

name: Corkscrew Squats
precautions: Do not go deeper than comfortable hip range.
Do not rush the rotation.
cues: Slowly rotate the knee inward at the bottom of the squat.
Keep the torso upright.

name: Banded Squats
precautions: Do not let the knees collapse inward.
Do not use a band so tight it forces unnatural knee tracking.
cues: Push the knees outward against the band constantly.
Maintain full foot contact with the floor.

name: Spanish Squats
precautions: Do not let the band tension ease up during the set.
Do not let the hips drop too low (keep it a quad-dominant movement).
cues: Keep the torso perfectly upright.
Drive knees aggressively forward past the toes (perpendicular to floor).
Squeeze quads hard at the top.

name: Johnson Calf Raises
precautions: Do not straighten the knees.
Do not use excessive weight.
cues: Keep knees bent at 90 degrees (or slightly less).
Focus on driving the ball of the foot down.
Achieve full range of motion.

name: Tibialis Raises
precautions: Do not use momentum.
Do not round the lower back.
cues: Initiate movement by pulling toes toward the shins.
Control the descent slowly (eccentric focus).

name: Heel Walk
precautions: Do not rush the movement.
cues: Keep knees straight.
Walk only on the heels, keeping the toes elevated.

name: Bent-Knee Calf Raises
precautions: Do not lock out knees.
Do not use excessive weight.
cues: Keep knees bent at 90 degrees.
Focus on maximum soleus squeeze.
Maintain a slow, controlled tempo.

name: Standing Calf Raises
precautions: Do not bounce at the bottom.
Do not let the feet roll outward.
cues: Keep legs straight.
Achieve full stretch at the bottom and full contraction at the top.

name: Squats
precautions: Do not round the lower back.
Do not let the knees cave inward.
cues: Initiate the movement by pushing the hips back.
Drive the knees out over the toes.
Maintain an upright torso and tight core.
